## Getting Started

First make sure you have the lab CLI toolbox installed:

```bash
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/sciminds/sci/main/install.sh | sh
```

And that it's up-to-date:

```bash
sci update && sci doctor
```

Then set up the Python environment:

```bash
cd {{.ProjectName}}/
{{- if eq .PkgManager "pixi"}}
pixi install
pixi run setup
{{- else}}
uv sync
uv run poe setup
{{- end}}
```

Then open in your editor and install the recommended extensions.

## Project Structure

```
code/
{{- if eq .DocSystem "quarto"}}
    report.qmd         # Quarto document → renders to PDF via Typst
    bibliography.bib   # BibTeX references
    templates/         # Typst template partials for PDF layout
{{- else if eq .DocSystem "myst"}}
    report.md          # MyST Markdown document (executable)
    bibliography.bib   # BibTeX references
{{- end}}
    notebooks/         # Marimo analysis notebooks
data/
    raw/               # raw data files
    derivatives/       # processed outputs
figs/                  # generated figures (referenced by report)
{{- if eq .DocSystem "myst"}}
myst.yml               # MyST project configuration
{{- end}}
```

## Workflow
{{if eq .DocSystem "quarto"}}
1. **Analyze** — work in `code/notebooks/` with Marimo, save figures to `figs/`
2. **Write** — reference figures in `code/report.qmd`, cite with `@key`
3. **Render** — generate PDF with the render task
{{- else if eq .DocSystem "myst"}}
1. **Analyze** — work in `code/notebooks/` with Marimo, save figures to `figs/`
2. **Write** — reference figures in `code/report.md`, cite with `` {cite}`key` ``
3. **Preview** — live-preview with the docs-start task
4. **Export** — generate PDF with the docs-pdf task
{{- else}}
1. **Analyze** — iterate on notebooks in `code/notebooks/`, save outputs to `figs/` and `data/derivatives/`
{{- end}}

